result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (3rd) and Operating w/ PAC (3rd). The defendant was found guilty of OWI (3rd) and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (3rd) was dismissed by the court.

  • Victoria Ann Dolderer was found guilty of OWI (3rd), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Prior to re-licensing the defendant is to complete an OWI Assessment.

miscConds.notes: Cash Bond previously posted in the amount of $900.00 has been applied.  The remaining balance is to be paid directly to the Waushara County Clerk of Court within 60 days or establish a payment plan.  Failure to pay may result in suspension of your driver's license, tax intercept, a civil judgment being entered against you, a warrant being issued for your arrest for contempt and/or the debt being turned over to a collection agency.
DNA Surcharge - See Comments noted above for the Fine.

The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars unless in furtherance of her employment, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician.
DNA sample to be provided and surcharge assessed.
Defendant to undergo an alcohol and other drug assessment and comply with any further counseling and/or treatment as deemed appropriate by the supervising agent.

timeConds.notes: Good Time Credit and Huber Privileges granted.  Sentence to commence forthwith.  Pursuant to s. 346.65(7), Defendant shall be required to remain in the County Jail for not less than a 48 consecutive hour period prior to release for Huber.

records.addlTxt: Case Called @ 3:20 PM: Defendant Victoria Ann Dolderer in court.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Resolution recited by DA.  Def confirms resolution and understands she must commence her sentence today.    Defendant advised of right to counsel and expertise.  Voluntary waiver of counsel accepted by Court.  Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Agrees with 2 prior convictions as recited by Court.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed. Plea OWI 3:  NC  Court accepts plea and enters JOC.  Ct 2 dismissed outright.  15TR-2558 DRI.  Upon motion of the State, orders reopening and vacature of the IC violation 15TR-2505 - reopened and dismissed.  Statement by Def:  None offered.  The Court:  Accepts resolution as appropriate.  S/W - 2 yrs probation.  Conditions:  45 days WCJ - Commence today immediately following SEH hrg, GT and Huber Privileges, mandatory 48 consecutive hr service prior to release for Huber, AODA and any follow thru as recommended;  the defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars unless in furtherance of her employment, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician; $1744.00 Fine, no blood draw fee; 24 mos DL Rev/IID for 24 mos upon licensure, advised to obtain OCC DL as soon as she can; OWI assessment prior to relicensing,  DNA Sample and Surcharge ordered by the Court.  Defendant advised of right to expunge DNA record through the Department of Justice.  1 day TS credit.  Appeal Rights Given.

Pre-trial conference at 11-12-2015 10:15 am.
Status conference at 12-08-2015 10:20 am.

The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars unless in furtherance of her employment at the Red Fox located in Wild Rose, WI, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician.   No operation of any motor vehicles without a valid driver's license.
